
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-yusef-sipcore-key-derivation-00.txt'>
    <title>"Key-Derivation Authentication Scheme", Rifaat Shekh-Yusef</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-yusef-sipcore-key-derivation-00.txt</link>
    <description>This document defines a Key-Derivation Authentication Scheme, based on the PBKDF2 Key Derivation Function (KDF), that could be used with the challenge-response authentication framework used by SIP to authenticate the user.  The scheme allows two parties to establish a mutually authenticated communication channel based on a shared password, without ever sending the password on the wire.</description>
    <dc:date>2014-10-10T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
